      • calculateProjectMappings

        public ProjectMapping[] calculateProjectMappings(ServerDetails serverDetails,
                                                 java.util.List<java.lang.String> paths,
                                                 java.lang.String projectIdOrAlias,
                                                 java.lang.String branch)
                                          throws ServiceCallException
        Tries to calculate the project and prefix mapping for the given files and optionally project.

        To prevent 214: URI too large Errors the paths are normally sent via POST request. In case the server does not support this (APIVersion < 7), it collects as many paths as fit into MAPPINGS_GET_REQUEST_PATH_CUTOFF_LENGTH and then sends them via GET

        Specified by:
        calculateProjectMappings in interface IIdeServiceClient
        Parameters:
        serverDetails - Server connection information
        paths - A list of relative file paths
        projectIdOrAlias - The project id for which to search the mapping. Can be null if the project is not known.
        branch - The repository branch name.
        Throws:
        ServiceCallException - if the service call fails
